msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../P/plaid-screen.rst:9
msgid ""
"[XEROX PARC] A ‘special effect’ that occurs when certain kinds of "
":ref:`memory-smash`\\es overwrite the control blocks or image memory of a "
"bit-mapped display. The term \"salt and pepper\" may refer to a different "
"pattern of similar origin. Though the term as coined at PARC refers to the "
"result of an error, some of the :ref:`X` demos induce plaid-screen effects "
"deliberately as a :ref:`display-hack`\\."
msgstr ""
"[XEROX PARC]ある種の\\ :ref:`memory-smash`\\ "
"がビットマップディスプレイの制御ブロックや画像メモリを上書きするときに起こる‘特殊効果’。\"salt and "
"pepper\"という用語は、似た由来の異なるパターンを指すことがある。PARCで作られたこの用語はエラーの結果を指すが、\\ :ref:`X`\\ "
"のデモのいくつかは、\\ :ref:`display-hack`\\ としてわざとplaid-screen効果を引き起こす。"
